STEP 1 -  db (dynamodb)
table name - Orders
partition key - OrderId

STEP 2 - then 2 lambda's GET and POST lambda

api for both's

create resource first make the 

resource name - storeOrder
method - POST  (proxy integration) - attach post lambda

resource name  - orders
method - GET  (proxy integration) - attach get lambda

STEP 3 - S3 bucket 

Bucket Versioning - On
permission tab - Block public access (off)
permission tab - Bucket policy (attach policy to allow lambda to put object in bucket)
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": "*",
            "Action": "s3:GetObject",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::web-page-yogita-rawat/*"
        }
    ]
}

Properties tab - 
Static website hosting - Enable
Index document - index.html

"upload all files - index.html, style.css, script.js , dashboard.html, dashboard.js, dashboard.css"



